{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":737,"text":"Human beings start putting each other into boxes"},{"time":3166,"text":"the second that they see each other --"},{"time":4983,"text":"Is that person dangerous? Are they attractive?"},{"time":8053,"text":"Are they a potential mate? Are they a potential networking opportunity?"},{"time":11319,"text":"We do this little interrogation when we meet people"},{"time":13853,"text":"to make a mental resume for them."},{"time":16020,"text":"What's your name? Where are you from?"},{"time":17537,"text":"How old are you? What do you do?"},{"time":20898,"text":"Then we get more personal with it."},{"time":23699,"text":"Have you ever had any diseases?"},{"time":26847,"text":"Have you ever been divorced?"},{"time":28834,"text":"Does your breath smell bad while you're answering my interrogation right now?"},{"time":32280,"text":"What are you into? Who are you into?"},{"time":33997,"text":"What gender do you like to sleep with?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":35863,"text":"I get it."},{"time":38293,"text":"We are neurologically hardwired"},{"time":40045,"text":"to seek out people like ourselves."},{"time":42429,"text":"We start forming cliques as soon as we're old enough"},{"time":44614,"text":"to know what acceptance feels like."},{"time":46547,"text":"We bond together based on anything that we can --"},{"time":48897,"text":"music preference, race, gender, the block that we grew up on."},{"time":54349,"text":"We seek out environments that reinforce our personal choices."},{"time":61237,"text":"Sometimes, though, just the question \"what do you do?\""},{"time":63698,"text":"can feel like somebody's opening a tiny little box"},{"time":65658,"text":"and asking you to squeeze yourself inside of it."},{"time":67187,"text":"Because the categories, I've found, are too limiting."},{"time":70754,"text":"The boxes are too narrow."},{"time":72638,"text":"And this can get really dangerous."}]},{"cues":[{"time":74755,"text":"So here's a disclaimer about me, though,"},{"time":76536,"text":"before we get too deep into this."},{"time":78138,"text":"I grew up in a very sheltered environment."},{"time":81123,"text":"I was raised in downtown Manhattan in the early 1980s,"},{"time":85069,"text":"two blocks from the epicenter of punk music."},{"time":88964,"text":"I was shielded from the pains of bigotry"},{"time":91054,"text":"and the social restrictions of a religiously-based upbringing."},{"time":95154,"text":"Where I come from, if you weren't a drag queen or a radical thinker"},{"time":98575,"text":"or a performance artist of some kind,"},{"time":100703,"text":"you were the weirdo."},{"time":102687,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":103970,"text":"It was an unorthodox upbringing,"},{"time":106055,"text":"but as a kid on the streets of New York,"},{"time":108566,"text":"you learn how to trust your own instincts,"},{"time":110537,"text":"you learn how to go with your own ideas."}]},{"cues":[{"time":113470,"text":"So when I was six, I decided that I wanted to be a boy."},{"time":116709,"text":"I went to school one day and the kids wouldn't let me play basketball with them."},{"time":120176,"text":"They said they wouldn't let girls play."},{"time":121609,"text":"So I went home, and I shaved my head,"},{"time":123019,"text":"and I came back the next day and I said, \"I'm a boy.\""},{"time":125641,"text":"I mean, who knows, right?"},{"time":126655,"text":"When you're six, maybe you can do that."},{"time":130468,"text":"I didn't want anyone to know that I was a girl, and they didn't."},{"time":134101,"text":"I kept up the charade for eight years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":136743,"text":"So this is me when I was 11."},{"time":140910,"text":"I was playing a kid named Walter"},{"time":142421,"text":"in a movie called \"Julian Po.\""},{"time":144610,"text":"I was a little street tough that followed Christian Slater around and badgered him."},{"time":148044,"text":"See, I was also a child actor,"},{"time":150094,"text":"which doubled up the layers of the performance of my identity,"},{"time":152776,"text":"because no one knew that I was actually a girl really playing a boy."},{"time":158864,"text":"In fact, no one in my life knew that I was a girl --"},{"time":161980,"text":"not my teachers at school, not my friends,"},{"time":164296,"text":"not the directors that I worked with."},{"time":166148,"text":"Kids would often come up to me in class"},{"time":168413,"text":"and grab me by the throat to check for an Adam's apple"},{"time":170647,"text":"or grab my crotch to check what I was working with."},{"time":173996,"text":"When I would go to the bathroom, I would turn my shoes around in the stalls"},{"time":176357,"text":"so that it looked like I was peeing standing up."},{"time":178912,"text":"At sleepovers I would have panic attacks"},{"time":180980,"text":"trying to break it to girls that they didn't want to kiss me"},{"time":183364,"text":"without outing myself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":185096,"text":"It's worth mentioning though"},{"time":187148,"text":"that I didn't hate my body or my genitalia."},{"time":190997,"text":"I didn't feel like I was in the wrong body."},{"time":192764,"text":"I felt like I was performing this elaborate act."},{"time":194796,"text":"I wouldn't have qualified as transgender."},{"time":198623,"text":"If my family, though, had been the kind of people to believe in therapy,"},{"time":200869,"text":"they probably would have diagnosed me"},{"time":202592,"text":"as something like gender dysmorphic"},{"time":204378,"text":"and put me on hormones to stave off puberty."},{"time":206781,"text":"But in my particular case,"},{"time":207665,"text":"I just woke up one day when I was 14,"},{"time":209380,"text":"and I decided that I wanted to be a girl again."},{"time":211963,"text":"Puberty had hit, and I had no idea what being a girl meant,"},{"time":214963,"text":"and I was ready to figure out who I actually was."}]},{"cues":[{"time":218588,"text":"When a kid behaves like I did,"},{"time":220993,"text":"they don't exactly have to come out, right?"},{"time":222829,"text":"No one is exactly shocked."},{"time":225090,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":228834,"text":"But I wasn't asked to define myself by my parents."},{"time":233297,"text":"When I was 15, and I called my father"},{"time":235163,"text":"to tell him that I had fallen in love,"},{"time":236863,"text":"it was the last thing on either of our minds"},{"time":239163,"text":"to discuss what the consequences were"},{"time":240779,"text":"of the fact that my first love was a girl."},{"time":243197,"text":"Three years later, when I fell in love with a man,"},{"time":245479,"text":"neither of my parents batted an eyelash either."},{"time":248063,"text":"See, it's one of the great blessings of my very unorthodox childhood"},{"time":251446,"text":"that I wasn't ever asked to define myself"},{"time":253480,"text":"as any one thing at any point."},{"time":255827,"text":"I was just allowed to be me, growing and changing in every moment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":259646,"text":"So four, almost five years ago,"},{"time":262691,"text":"Proposition 8, the great marriage equality debate,"},{"time":266006,"text":"was raising a lot of dust around this country."},{"time":267981,"text":"And at the time, getting married wasn't really something"},{"time":270592,"text":"I spent a lot of time thinking about."},{"time":271725,"text":"But I was struck by the fact that America,"},{"time":274531,"text":"a country with such a tarnished civil rights record,"},{"time":276596,"text":"could be repeating its mistakes so blatantly."},{"time":279212,"text":"And I remember watching the discussion on television"},{"time":281180,"text":"and thinking how interesting it was"},{"time":282981,"text":"that the separation of church and state"},{"time":286012,"text":"was essentially drawing geographical boundaries throughout this country,"},{"time":289631,"text":"between places where people believed in it"},{"time":291213,"text":"and places where people didn't."},{"time":292998,"text":"And then, that this discussion was drawing geographical boundaries around me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":299246,"text":"If this was a war with two disparate sides,"},{"time":302364,"text":"I, by default, fell on team gay,"},{"time":305145,"text":"because I certainly wasn't 100 percent straight."},{"time":308331,"text":"At the time I was just beginning to emerge"},{"time":311580,"text":"from this eight-year personal identity crisis zigzag"},{"time":315497,"text":"that saw me go from being a boy"},{"time":317330,"text":"to being this awkward girl that looked like a boy in girl's clothes"},{"time":320552,"text":"to the opposite extreme of this super skimpy,"},{"time":323342,"text":"over-compensating, boy-chasing girly-girl"},{"time":326008,"text":"to finally just a hesitant exploration of what I actually was,"},{"time":329976,"text":"a tomboyish girl"},{"time":332383,"text":"who liked both boys and girls depending on the person."}]},{"cues":[{"time":335592,"text":"I had spent a year photographing this new generation of girls, much like myself,"},{"time":340743,"text":"who fell kind of between-the-lines --"},{"time":342409,"text":"girls who skateboarded but did it in lacy underwear,"},{"time":345946,"text":"girls who had boys' haircuts but wore girly nail polish,"},{"time":349904,"text":"girls who had eyeshadow to match their scraped knees,"},{"time":352899,"text":"girls who liked girls and boys who all liked boys and girls"},{"time":355997,"text":"who all hated being boxed in to anything."},{"time":357846,"text":"I loved these people, and I admired their freedom,"},{"time":361597,"text":"but I watched as the world outside of our utopian bubble"},{"time":364530,"text":"exploded into these raging debates"},{"time":366380,"text":"where pundits started likening our love to bestiality on national television."},{"time":371946,"text":"And this powerful awareness rolled in over me"},{"time":374279,"text":"that I was a minority, and in my own home country,"},{"time":379646,"text":"based on one facet of my character."},{"time":382297,"text":"I was legally and indisputably a second-class citizen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":387912,"text":"I was not an activist."},{"time":389446,"text":"I wave no flags in my own life."},{"time":391946,"text":"But I was plagued by this question:"},{"time":394085,"text":"How could anyone vote to strip the rights"},{"time":397031,"text":"of the vast variety of people that I knew"},{"time":399196,"text":"based on one element of their character?"},{"time":402630,"text":"How could they say that we as a group"},{"time":404146,"text":"were not deserving of equal rights as somebody else?"},{"time":407079,"text":"Were we even a group? What group?"},{"time":409446,"text":"And had these people ever even consciously met a victim of their discrimination?"},{"time":413313,"text":"Did they know who they were voting against and what the impact was?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":417356,"text":"And then it occurred to me,"},{"time":419247,"text":"perhaps if they could look into the eyes"},{"time":421530,"text":"of the people that they were casting into second-class citizenship"},{"time":425311,"text":"it might make it harder for them to do."},{"time":427213,"text":"It might give them pause."},{"time":429197,"text":"Obviously I couldn't get 20 million people to the same dinner party,"},{"time":435037,"text":"so I figured out a way where I could introduce them to each other photographically"},{"time":439368,"text":"without any artifice, without any lighting,"},{"time":442334,"text":"or without any manipulation of any kind on my part."},{"time":445568,"text":"Because in a photograph you can examine a lion's whiskers"},{"time":448318,"text":"without the fear of him ripping your face off."}]},{"cues":[{"time":451034,"text":"For me, photography is not just about exposing film,"},{"time":454431,"text":"it's about exposing the viewer"},{"time":456384,"text":"to something new, a place they haven't gone before,"},{"time":458485,"text":"but most importantly, to people that they might be afraid of."},{"time":461800,"text":"Life magazine introduced generations of people"},{"time":463644,"text":"to distant, far-off cultures they never knew existed through pictures."},{"time":467718,"text":"So I decided to make a series of very simple portraits,"},{"time":473951,"text":"mugshots if you will."},{"time":475701,"text":"And I basically decided to photograph anyone in this country"},{"time":479469,"text":"that was not 100 percent straight,"},{"time":481870,"text":"which, if you don't know, is a limitless number of people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":485053,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":487103,"text":"So this was a very large undertaking,"},{"time":489769,"text":"and to do it we needed some help."},{"time":491653,"text":"So I ran out in the freezing cold,"},{"time":494186,"text":"and I photographed every single person that I knew that I could get to"},{"time":497594,"text":"in February of about two years ago."},{"time":501564,"text":"And I took those photographs, and I went to the HRC and I asked them for some help."},{"time":505687,"text":"And they funded two weeks of shooting in New York."},{"time":508053,"text":"And then we made this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":511064,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":523341,"text":"Video: I'm iO Tillett Wright, and I'm an artist born and raised in New York City."},{"time":527524,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":540832,"text":"Self Evident Truths is a photographic record of LGBTQ America today."},{"time":545494,"text":"My aim is to take a simple portrait"},{"time":547117,"text":"of anyone who's anything other than 100 percent straight"},{"time":549767,"text":"or feels like they fall in the LGBTQ spectrum in any way."},{"time":554987,"text":"My goal is to show the humanity that exists in every one of us"},{"time":557985,"text":"through the simplicity of a face."},{"time":560103,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":562791,"text":"\"We hold these truths to be self-evident that all men are created equal.\""},{"time":565881,"text":"It's written in the Declaration of Independence."},{"time":568298,"text":"We are failing as a nation"},{"time":569565,"text":"to uphold the morals upon which we were founded."},{"time":571674,"text":"There is no equality in the United States."}]},{"cues":[{"time":573896,"text":"[\"What does equality mean to you?\"]"},{"time":576279,"text":"[\"Marriage\"] [\"Freedom\"] [\"Civil rights\"]"},{"time":577917,"text":"[\"Treat every person as you'd treat yourself\"]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":580043,"text":"It's when you don't have to think about it, simple as that."},{"time":583663,"text":"The fight for equal rights is not just about gay marriage."},{"time":586453,"text":"Today in 29 states, more than half of this country,"},{"time":590549,"text":"you can legally be fired just for your sexuality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":594920,"text":"[\"Who is responsible for equality?\"]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":598071,"text":"I've heard hundreds of people give the same answer:"},{"time":601082,"text":"\"We are all responsible for equality.\""},{"time":604558,"text":"So far we've shot 300 faces in New York City."},{"time":607411,"text":"And we wouldn't have been able to do any of it"},{"time":608827,"text":"without the generous support of the Human Rights Campaign."},{"time":611712,"text":"I want to take the project across the country."},{"time":613661,"text":"I want to visit 25 American cities, and I want to shoot 4,000 or 5,000 people."},{"time":617744,"text":"This is my contribution to the civil rights fight of my generation."},{"time":621727,"text":"I challenge you to look into the faces of these people"},{"time":623904,"text":"and tell them that they deserve less than any other human being."},{"time":626766,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":628806,"text":"[\"Self evident truths\"]"},{"time":631088,"text":"[\"4,000 faces across America\"]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":632753,"text":"(Music)"},{"time":637309,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":645557,"text":"iO Tillett Wright: Absolutely nothing could have prepared us for what happened after that."},{"time":649840,"text":"Almost 85,000 people watched that video,"},{"time":653090,"text":"and then they started emailing us from all over the country,"},{"time":655590,"text":"asking us to come to their towns and help them to show their faces."},{"time":660257,"text":"And a lot more people wanted to show their faces than I had anticipated."},{"time":664607,"text":"So I changed my immediate goal to 10,000 faces."},{"time":668108,"text":"That video was made in the spring of 2011,"},{"time":672173,"text":"and as of today I have traveled to almost 20 cities"},{"time":675630,"text":"and photographed almost 2,000 people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":678536,"text":"I know that this is a talk,"},{"time":681546,"text":"but I'd like to have a minute of just quiet"},{"time":684812,"text":"and have you just look at these faces"},{"time":686061,"text":"because there is nothing that I can say that will add to them."},{"time":689931,"text":"Because if a picture is worth a thousand words,"},{"time":692464,"text":"then a picture of a face needs a whole new vocabulary."}]},{"cues":[{"time":717069,"text":"So after traveling and talking to people"},{"time":720748,"text":"in places like Oklahoma or small-town Texas,"},{"time":724596,"text":"we found evidence that the initial premise was dead on."},{"time":728131,"text":"Visibility really is key."},{"time":730017,"text":"Familiarity really is the gateway drug to empathy."},{"time":733280,"text":"Once an issue pops up in your own backyard or amongst your own family,"},{"time":736730,"text":"you're far more likely to explore sympathy for it"},{"time":739647,"text":"or explore a new perspective on it."},{"time":741213,"text":"Of course, in my travels I met people"},{"time":743864,"text":"who legally divorced their children for being other than straight,"},{"time":748063,"text":"but I also met people who were Southern Baptists"},{"time":750431,"text":"who switched churches because their child was a lesbian."},{"time":753447,"text":"Sparking empathy had become the backbone of Self Evident Truths."}]},{"cues":[{"time":757597,"text":"But here's what I was starting to learn that was really interesting:"},{"time":761013,"text":"Self Evident Truths doesn't erase the differences between us."},{"time":765363,"text":"In fact, on the contrary, it highlights them."},{"time":768747,"text":"It presents, not just the complexities"},{"time":770846,"text":"found in a procession of different human beings,"},{"time":773013,"text":"but the complexities found within each individual person."},{"time":776613,"text":"It wasn't that we had too many boxes, it was that we had too few."}]},{"cues":[{"time":787518,"text":"At some point I realized that my mission to photograph \"gays\" was inherently flawed,"},{"time":794303,"text":"because there were a million different shades of gay."},{"time":797491,"text":"Here I was trying to help,"},{"time":800237,"text":"and I had perpetuated the very thing I had spent my life trying to avoid --"},{"time":803430,"text":"yet another box."},{"time":805936,"text":"At some point I added a question to the release form"},{"time":809156,"text":"that asked people to quantify themselves"},{"time":811085,"text":"on a scale of one to 100 percent gay."},{"time":813885,"text":"And I watched so many existential crises unfold in front of me."},{"time":817801,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":820602,"text":"People didn't know what to do"},{"time":821802,"text":"because they had never been presented with the option before."},{"time":824205,"text":"Can you quantify your openness?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":826392,"text":"Once they got over the shock, though,"},{"time":828302,"text":"by and large people opted for somewhere between 70 to 95 percent"},{"time":832385,"text":"or the 3 to 20 percent marks."},{"time":834902,"text":"Of course, there were lots of people who opted for a 100 percent one or the other,"},{"time":837603,"text":"but I found that a much larger proportion of people"},{"time":840071,"text":"identified as something that was much more nuanced."},{"time":842920,"text":"I found that most people fall on a spectrum of what I have come to refer to as \"Grey.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":849129,"text":"Let me be clear though -- and this is very important --"},{"time":853113,"text":"in no way am I saying that preference doesn't exist."},{"time":857829,"text":"And I am not even going to address the issue of choice versus biological imperative,"},{"time":862629,"text":"because if any of you happen to be of the belief"},{"time":865496,"text":"that sexual orientation is a choice,"},{"time":867363,"text":"I invite you to go out and try to be grey."},{"time":868896,"text":"I'll take your picture just for trying."},{"time":871162,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":872545,"text":"What I am saying though is that human beings are not one-dimensional."},{"time":876962,"text":"The most important thing to take from the percentage system is this:"},{"time":882730,"text":"If you have gay people over here"},{"time":884947,"text":"and you have straight people over here,"},{"time":888595,"text":"and while we recognize that most people identify"},{"time":891563,"text":"as somewhere closer to one binary or another,"},{"time":894266,"text":"there is this vast spectrum of people that exist in between."}]},{"cues":[{"time":899212,"text":"And the reality that this presents is a complicated one."},{"time":902246,"text":"Because, for example, if you pass a law"},{"time":904530,"text":"that allows a boss to fire an employee for homosexual behavior,"},{"time":908033,"text":"where exactly do you draw the line?"},{"time":910800,"text":"Is it over here, by the people who have had one or two heterosexual experiences so far?"},{"time":916666,"text":"Or is it over here"},{"time":917967,"text":"by the people who have only had one or two homosexual experiences thus far?"},{"time":922066,"text":"Where exactly does one become a second-class citizen?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":926716,"text":"Another interesting thing that I learned from my project and my travels"},{"time":931532,"text":"is just what a poor binding agent sexual orientation is."},{"time":935834,"text":"After traveling so much and meeting so many people,"},{"time":938445,"text":"let me tell you, there are just as many jerks and sweethearts"},{"time":941950,"text":"and Democrats and Republicans and jocks and queens"},{"time":944899,"text":"and every other polarization you can possibly think of"},{"time":947849,"text":"within the LGBT community"},{"time":949983,"text":"as there are within the human race."},{"time":953499,"text":"Aside from the fact that we play with one legal hand tied behind our backs,"},{"time":958117,"text":"and once you get past the shared narrative of prejudice and struggle,"},{"time":961782,"text":"just being other than straight"},{"time":963183,"text":"doesn't necessarily mean that we have anything in common."}]},{"cues":[{"time":968199,"text":"So in the endless proliferation of faces that Self Evident Truths is always becoming,"},{"time":976600,"text":"as it hopefully appears across more and more platforms,"},{"time":979799,"text":"bus shelters, billboards, Facebook pages, screen savers,"},{"time":985258,"text":"perhaps in watching this procession of humanity,"},{"time":988333,"text":"something interesting and useful will begin to happen."},{"time":991250,"text":"Hopefully these categories, these binaries,"},{"time":994967,"text":"these over-simplified boxes"},{"time":996716,"text":"will begin to become useless and they'll begin to fall away."},{"time":1001782,"text":"Because really, they describe nothing that we see"},{"time":1005200,"text":"and no one that we know and nothing that we are."},{"time":1008549,"text":"What we see are human beings in all their multiplicity."},{"time":1014150,"text":"And seeing them makes it harder to deny their humanity."},{"time":1017733,"text":"At the very least I hope it makes it harder to deny their human rights."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1022074,"text":"So is it me particularly"},{"time":1025633,"text":"that you would choose to deny the right to housing,"},{"time":1029135,"text":"the right to adopt children, the right to marriage,"},{"time":1032116,"text":"the freedom to shop here, live here, buy here?"},{"time":1035749,"text":"Am I the one that you choose to disown"},{"time":1037828,"text":"as your child or your brother or your sister or your mother or your father,"},{"time":1042250,"text":"your neighbor, your cousin, your uncle, the president,"},{"time":1044598,"text":"your police woman or the fireman?"},{"time":1048048,"text":"It's too late."},{"time":1051066,"text":"Because I already am all of those things."},{"time":1054367,"text":"We already are all of those things, and we always have been."},{"time":1058732,"text":"So please don't greet us as strangers,"},{"time":1061538,"text":"greet us as your fellow human beings, period."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1065091,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1066407,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}